The paper discusses a scenario where a random signal is processed to produce a control signal, which is further processed to produce a third sequence. This involves communication and coordination, which are key topics in information theory (cs.IT), multimedia (cs.MM), and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses causality constraints and strategic play, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and game theory (cs.GT).
